history.text: Hello
hi have you watched the movie maleficent?
Yes but it was a few years ago.
yea i watched it when it came out in 2014
I know Angelina Jolie and Elle Fanning are in it
i really liked how it told the story of sleeping beauty from the perspective of maleficent
Yeah it was different. Who directed it?
robert sterling. i cant believe it got such low ratings though
Eh, I wasn't too crazy about it either. What did Rotten Tomatoes and other online reviewers give it?
51% on rotten tomatoes, 56/100 metacritic, cinemascore gave it an A though
Interesting. What genre is it classified as?
oddly enough it is classified as a superhero movie
That's very strange, haha. What was your favorite part about the movie?
my favorite part was when the guy was supposed to kill maleficent but instead decided to just cut off her wings
how about you?
Yeah that was pretty messed up.
it was pretty interesting that they had maleficent be auroras fairy godmother
Yeah it was. I thought it was interesting that she is the one who actually got sleeping beauty out of her curse.
yea i guess i am biased because i am a disney buff but i did really enjoy the movie. i also liked how aurora wanted to help maleficent.
Yes I am too. What other critical reviews did it get?
it got some criticism for having bland backgrounds and only being entertaining due to angelina's portrayal as maleficent
Whoever did the costume design and her makeup did a great job though. If nothing else it's a unique retelling of a story.

yes especially the crazy twist at the end. i couldn't believe it was maleficent's kiss that broke the spell and not
 prince phillip!
Yes that was for sure interesting.
and then the charming prince actually becomes the bad guy! it was like an emotional roller coaster
Yeah that was twist. What were some other key scenes?

well, when prince phillip was about to kill maleficent, aurora found maleficent's wings and released them. maleficent got her wings back but she couldn't bring herself to kill phillip. he then attacked her from behind and they both fell from the tower. i thought they were both going to die but maleficent was able to get away
I was glad she got her wings back, she was so devastated when they were cut off
